<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-494-978  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 494 978.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  July 1990 v7 n7 p206(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hookup. (Software Review) (Hip Software Corp. Hookup iconicprogramming packages for Macintosh) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cummings, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hip Software Corp's Hookup iconic program-development softwarelets users represent complex program logic in a graphical manner,but it lacks flexibility and editing features.andP;  The user can buildelaborate animated scenes and play music or sound effects with themouse.andP;  It presents the user with icons that represent programmingfunctions; the use drags the icons into position and links themwith 'wires.' Joining an input icon directly to an output iconallows simple interactive use.andP;  Users need a good grasp ofprogramming logic to obtain sophisticated results from HookUp, andthere is no Undo command to correct errors.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hip Software Corp. (products).andO;Product:   HookUp! (Program development software).andO;Topic:     Program Development ToolsEvaluationSoftware Packages.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>